            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ [ ¶ Specimen of Grass ¶ .— T. R, Samaria. ¶  - The grass sent is the British Brome (Bromus mollis). It is not a grass of prominent value, particularly in our climate, as it fails when most needed, ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.12.00c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To the Leader</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Answers to correspondents', <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg>, 14 December 1895, p. 9.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>[<seg style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Specimen of Grass</seg>.— T. R, Samaria.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
               </note> - The grass sent is the British Brome (<name key="Bromus%20mollis">Bromus mollis</name>). It is not a grass of prominent value, particularly in our climate, as it fails when most needed, during the hottest time of the<seg style=""> season, being an annual without much rigor</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                     <p rend="Footnote"
                        style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Typesetter's error for</seg> vigor?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> or succulence to withstand dryness. "It has, however," Baron von Mueller remarks, "the merit of easy natural dissemination, and of the capability of living on poor soil, so that in sterile regions, not too hot, it would help to furnish pasturage."]</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Bromus%20mollis">Bromus mollis</name>
            </p>
